        <body>
      
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Mobile</placeName> <date>July 2<hi rend="sup">nd</hi> 1852</date></p>
			<p><addressee>Rev Mr Isaac Leeser</addressee>&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
          <p rend="indent(4)">Dear Sir</p>
			<p>You will<lb/> confer a favor by informing me<lb/> if possible by return mail. If<lb/> there is a first rate Hebrew Boarding<lb/> School for Young Ladies in <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>&#44;<lb/> as I have an Idea of Putting<lb/> my Daughter <persName>Adelaide</persName> to school at<lb/> the north &#38; anticipate leaving here in<lb/> about Three weeks for your quarter&#63;</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">We have completed the<lb/> purchase of a fine Building &#38; made<lb/> contracts to complete the same for<lb/> a <sic>beautifull</sic> synagogue which we<lb/> anticipate consecrating about next<lb/> <date>January</date>. <persName>Rev Julius Eckman</persName> of<lb/> <placeName>Charleston</placeName> &#38; <persName>I Jacobs</persName> of <placeName>Baltimore</placeName> are<lb/> applicants for the office of minister.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I have also the pleasure<lb/> of informing you that my Daughter<lb/> <persName>Sarah</persName> is engaged to get married<lb/> to <persName>Mr Joseph Morrison</persName> of this<lb/> place. Excuse this hasty<lb/> scrawl &#38; believe me&#160;&#160;<persName role="author">Israel I. Jones</persName></p>
          
        </body>
    </text>
